result.execSummary:
The defendant Tiffany Sharee Rockwood was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating While Revoked (Rev due to alc/contr subst/refusal), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.44(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Cash Bond previously posted in the amount of $250.00 has been applied.  The remaining balance of the Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 2:47 PM: Defendant Tiffany Sharee Rockwood in court, appearing pro se.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per DA:  Believes matteris resolved with a waiver of counsel.  Def does have a valid DL and State will argue for guideline penalty which Def expects to argue.    Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Knowing and Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea (OAR):  NC  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.   Argument as to Penalty by DA. Statement by Def: Yes.  The Court:  Positive steps taken with valid DL.  Accepts recommendation as appropriate- Court Costs - 60 DTP or PP with application of cash bond posted.  5 days WCJ - Report 7/1/16 @ 8:00 PM - GT and Huber.  No TS Credit.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Appeal Rights Given
Status conference on June 3, 2016 at 02:30 pm.

Case Called @ 3:32 PM: Defendant Tiffany Sharee Rockwood in court.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Def produced a valid DL for State's review.  States she is willing to "waive" the 5 day WCJ offer and pay costs.    Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Def states she is not pleading NC today and states she intends to contact SPD for counsel. She states she is employed full time.  Based upon earnings the Court does not believe she will qualify for SPD services.  Court would consider a Court Appointment if she desired same.  She requests add'l time to obtain counsel.  In person STC scheduled - NOH Given.  Status conference scheduled for June 3, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
Plea/sentencing hearing on April 20, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license for the manner of operation.

Case Called @ 3:05 PM: Defendant Tiffany Sharee Rockwood in court, appearing pro se.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel.  Def does not wish counsel today.  NGP received and entered.   Def expects to reinstate her regular DL in the very near future.  P/S Scheduled - NOH Given.  Court enters Riverside Ruling in favor of the State and probable cause finding as to each count alleged within the complaint.  ADA confirms an offer letter will be sent directly to Defendant.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for April 20, 2016 at 02:30 pm.
